29/02/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Greek major opposition party New Democracy leader Costas Karamanlis sent a message of co-operation to the Turkish government on Saturday (28 February). Karamanlis, whose party has a good chance of winning Greek Parliamentary elections on 7 March, said would work hard for normalisation of relations.
Also on Saturday, International Olympic Committee President Jacques Rogge repeated that he has confidence in the ability of the Greek organisers to complete work on the Olympic venues in time. "Very much has been achieved, much remains to be done . I remain confident," he said. (ANA, MPA, AFP, Reuters - 28/02/04)
